// Data Loader
// Initializes all session artifacts (diagrams, documents, designs, spreadsheets, snippets)
// on session load. Loads artifact types in parallel, handles failures gracefully,
// and emits progress events to the window for UI feedback.

Progress events are dispatched as window CustomEvents under the key 'artifact-loading-progress'.
Each event detail has type: 'start' | 'artifact_loaded' | 'complete' | 'error'.

Retry config: up to 2 retries, starting at 500ms delay (exponential backoff).

FUNCTION dispatchLoadingProgress(progress)                              EXPORT
  Dispatch a CustomEvent('artifact-loading-progress') to window with the given progress detail.

---

FUNCTION retryWithBackoff(fn, config) -> Promise<T> [private]
  Attempt fn() up to maxRetries+1 times.
  On each failure (except the last), wait delayMs * 2^attempt before retrying.
  On final failure, throw the last error.

---

FUNCTION loadDiagrams(project, session) -> Promise<Diagram[]>           EXPORT
  CALLS: retryWithBackoff (data-loader), getDiagrams (api), setDiagrams (sessionStore), dispatchLoadingProgress (data-loader)
  Fetch diagrams via api.getDiagrams with retry. Store in sessionStore.
  Dispatch an artifact_loaded progress event.
  On failure: log the error, dispatch an error event, store an empty array, and return [].

---

FUNCTION loadDocuments(project, session) -> Promise<Document[]>         EXPORT
  CALLS: retryWithBackoff (data-loader), getDocuments (api), setDocuments (sessionStore), dispatchLoadingProgress (data-loader)
  Same pattern as loadDiagrams.

---

FUNCTION loadDesigns(project, session) -> Promise<Design[]>             EXPORT
  CALLS: retryWithBackoff (data-loader), getDesigns (api), setDesigns (sessionStore), dispatchLoadingProgress (data-loader)
  Same pattern as loadDiagrams.

---

FUNCTION loadSpreadsheets(project, session) -> Promise<Spreadsheet[]>   EXPORT
  CALLS: retryWithBackoff (data-loader), getSpreadsheets (api), setSpreadsheets (sessionStore), dispatchLoadingProgress (data-loader)
  Same pattern as loadDiagrams.

---

FUNCTION loadSnippets(project, session) -> Promise<Snippet[]>           EXPORT
  CALLS: retryWithBackoff (data-loader), getSnippets (api), setSnippets (sessionStore), dispatchLoadingProgress (data-loader)
  Same pattern as loadDiagrams.

---

FUNCTION loadAllArtifacts(project, session) -> Promise<summary>         EXPORT
  CALLS: loadDiagrams (data-loader), loadDocuments (data-loader), loadDesigns (data-loader), loadSpreadsheets (data-loader), loadSnippets (data-loader), dispatchLoadingProgress (data-loader)
  Dispatch a 'start' progress event.
  Load all five artifact types in parallel via Promise.all.
  Compute total artifact count.
  Dispatch a 'complete' event with the total count.
  Return { totalArtifacts, diagrams, documents, designs, spreadsheets, snippets }.
  IF a critical error occurs: dispatch error event and return whatever was already stored in sessionStore.

---

FUNCTION onLoadingProgress(callback) -> cleanup                         EXPORT
  Subscribe to 'artifact-loading-progress' window events.
  Call the callback with each event's detail.
  Return a cleanup function that removes the listener.
